The paper proposes a new variant of LSTM for next POI recommendation, which is a sequential recommendation task. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), which focuses on developing and improving machine learning algorithms. 

The paper also deals with location-based data and social networks, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with search and recommendation systems. 

Moreover, the paper introduces a new model that captures the spatio-temporal relation between successive check-ins, which involves both spatial and temporal data. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with modeling and analyzing social networks and their interactions with information systems. 

Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed model using real-world datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering), which deals with developing and evaluating software systems. 

Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques, such as LSTM, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with developing and improving NLP algorithms.
